### Example 6: Solve for *x* in a formula — distance formula rearranged

If *d = rt* (distance = rate × time), and we know *d* and *r*, we can solve for *t*.

<!-- BUILD: given distance and rate, solve for time using division -->

```scheme
(define distance-rate-time-solve
  (lambda (d r)
    ;; d = rt, so t = d/r
    (/ d r)))

(define trip-distance 150)  ;; miles
(define trip-rate 60)       ;; mph

(display \"If distance d = \")
(display trip-distance)
(display \" miles and rate r = \")
(display trip-rate)
(display \" mph,\")
(newline)
(display \"then time t = d/r = \")
(display (distance-rate-time-solve trip-distance trip-rate))
(display \" hours\")
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"t = 2.5 hours\"]

