### Example 7: Word problem — tickets and money

You have $50. Tickets cost $8 each. How many can you buy? Set up *8x = 50* and solve.

<!-- BUILD: solve the word problem as a linear equation -->

```scheme
(define ticket-cost 8)
(define total-money 50)

(define max-tickets
  (floor (/ total-money ticket-cost)))

(display \"Tickets cost $\")
(display ticket-cost)
(display \" each. You have $\")
(display total-money)
(display \".\")
(newline)
(display \"Max tickets you can buy: \")
(display max-tickets)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"Max tickets you can buy: 6\"]

---

### Example 8: Celsius to Fahrenheit — solve for F

The formula is *F = (9/5)C + 32*. Given *C = 20*, solve for *F*.

<!-- BUILD: evaluate the formula with exact rational arithmetic -->

```scheme
(define celsius-to-fahrenheit
  (lambda (c)
    (let ((nine-fifths (exact/rat 9 5)))
      (+ (exact/->float (exact/* nine-fifths (exact/rat c 1))) 32))))

(define temp-c 20)

(display \"Temperature in Celsius: \")
(display temp-c)
(display \"°C\")
(newline)
(display \"Temperature in Fahrenheit: \")
(display (celsius-to-fahrenheit temp-c))
(display \"°F\")
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"68.0°F\"]

---

### Example 9: Solve an equation with negative solution

<!-- BUILD: solve -2x + 6 = 10 using sym/solve-linear -->

```scheme
(define eqn-neg-2x-plus-6
  (sym/poly 'x (list 6 -2)))  ;; 6 - 2x

(define solution-neg
  (sym/solve-linear eqn-neg-2x-plus-6 10))

(display \"Solve: -2x + 6 = 10\")
(newline)
(display \"Solution: x = \")
(display solution-neg)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"x = -2\"]

