### Example 10: Check a solution by substitution

Given *x = 5*, verify that it satisfies *4x - 7 = 13*.

<!-- BUILD: substitute x into the equation and check equality -->

```scheme
(define check-solution
  (lambda (x)
    (let ((left (- (* 4 x) 7))
          (right 13))
      (= left right))))

(define x-value 5)

(display \"Does x = \")
(display x-value)
(display \" satisfy 4x - 7 = 13?\")
(newline)
(display (if (check-solution x-value) \"Yes, it checks!\" \"No, it does not.\"))
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"Yes, it checks!\"]

