### Example 13: Distance between two points

The distance formula comes from the Pythagorean theorem: *d = √((x₂ - x₁)² + (y₂ - y₁)²)*.

<!-- BUILD: use geom/distance to find the distance between (0, 0) and (3, 4) -->

```scheme
(define origin (geom/point 0 0))
(define pt-3-4 (geom/point 3 4))

(define dist (geom/distance origin pt-3-4))

(display \"Distance from (0,0) to (3,4): \")
(display dist)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"Distance from (0,0) to (3,4): 5\"]

