### Example 22: Find where two lines intersect (solve system by hand)

Solve *y = 2x + 1* and *y = -x + 4* by setting them equal: *2x + 1 = -x + 4*.

<!-- BUILD: solve for x, then find y -->

```scheme
(define solve-intersection
  (let* ((eqn (sym/poly 'x (list -3 3)))  ;; 2x + 1 = -x + 4 → 3x - 3 = 0
         (x-val (sym/solve-linear eqn 0))
         (y-val (+ (* 2 x-val) 1)))
    (list x-val y-val)))

(display \"Intersection of y = 2x + 1 and y = -x + 4:\")
(newline)
(display \"x = \")
(display (list-ref solve-intersection 0))
(display \", y = \")
(display (list-ref solve-intersection 1))
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"x = 1, y = 3\"]

---

### Example 23: Plot the intersection point

<!-- BUILD: overlay the two lines and mark the intersection -->

```scheme
(define line1 (plot/function (lambda (x) (+ (* 2 x) 1)) -2 4))
(define line2 (plot/function (lambda (x) (+ (- x) 4)) -2 4))
(define intersection-point (plot/scatter (list 1) (list 3)))

(define intersection-plot
  (plot/with line1 line2 intersection-point))

(plot/render-svg intersection-plot)
```

[VISUAL: two lines crossing, with a dot marking the intersection at (1, 3)]

