### Example 32: Function composition — *f(g(x))*

If *f(x) = x + 1* and *g(x) = 2x*, then *f(g(x)) = 2x + 1*.

<!-- BUILD: compose two functions and evaluate -->

```scheme
(define f (lambda (x) (+ x 1)))
(define g (lambda (x) (* 2 x)))

(define f-of-g
  (lambda (x)
    (f (g x))))

(display \"f(x) = x + 1, g(x) = 2x\")
(newline)
(display \"f(g(3)) = f(6) = \")
(display (f-of-g 3))
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"f(g(3)) = 7\"]

