### Example 33: Inverse of a linear function

If *f(x) = 2x + 3*, the inverse *f⁻¹(y)* satisfies *f(f⁻¹(y)) = y*. Solve for it.

<!-- BUILD: derive and test an inverse function -->

```scheme
(define f (lambda (x) (+ (* 2 x) 3)))
(define f-inverse (lambda (y) (/ (- y 3) 2)))

(display \"f(x) = 2x + 3\")
(newline)
(display \"f⁻¹(y) = (y - 3) / 2\")
(newline)
(display \"Test: f(f⁻¹(11)) = \")
(display (f (f-inverse 11)))
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"f(f⁻¹(11)) = 11\"]

