### Example 51: Approximate square root by iteration (Babylonian method)

Given *a*, guess *x₀*, then iterate *xₙ₊₁ = (xₙ + a/xₙ)/2*.

<!-- BUILD: implement iterative square root for a = 10 -->

```scheme
(define babylonian-sqrt
  (lambda (a guess iterations)
    (if (= iterations 0)
        guess
        (babylonian-sqrt a
                         (/ (+ guess (/ a guess)) 2)
                         (- iterations 1)))))

(define approx-sqrt-10
  (babylonian-sqrt 10 3 5))

(display \"Approximate √10 (5 iterations, start at 3): \")
(display approx-sqrt-10)
(newline)
(display \"Actual √10: \")
(display (sqrt 10))
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing close approximation to 3.162...]

