### Example 60: Distance formula is Pythagorean theorem

Distance from (1, 2) to (4, 6) is √((4-1)² + (6-2)²).

<!-- BUILD: calculate by hand, then use geom/distance -->

```scheme
(define x1 1)
(define y1 2)
(define x2 4)
(define y2 6)

(define dx (- x2 x1))
(define dy (- y2 y1))
(define dist-manual (sqrt (+ (* dx dx) (* dy dy))))

(define pt1 (geom/point x1 y1))
(define pt2 (geom/point x2 y2))
(define dist-geom (geom/distance pt1 pt2))

(display \"Distance from (1,2) to (4,6):\")
(newline)
(display \"Manual: √(3² + 4²) = √25 = \")
(display dist-manual)
(newline)
(display \"Using geom/distance: \")
(display dist-geom)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing both methods give 5]

