### Example 61: Pythagorean theorem in 3D

Distance in 3D space: *√(Δx² + Δy² + Δz²)*.

<!-- BUILD: compute 3D distance manually -->

```scheme
(define x1 0)
(define y1 0)
(define z1 0)
(define x2 2)
(define y2 3)
(define z2 6)

(define dx (- x2 x1))
(define dy (- y2 y1))
(define dz (- z2 z1))

(define dist-3d (sqrt (+ (* dx dx) (* dy dy) (* dz dz))))

(display \"Distance from (0,0,0) to (2,3,6): \")
(display dist-3d)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"7\"]

