### Example 62: Check if a triangle is a right triangle given three sides

Given sides 7, 24, 25, check if it's a right triangle.

<!-- BUILD: verify a² + b² = c² for the largest side as hypotenuse -->

```scheme
(define sides (list 7 24 25))
(define sorted-sides (sort sides <))
(define a (list-ref sorted-sides 0))
(define b (list-ref sorted-sides 1))
(define c (list-ref sorted-sides 2))

(define is-right? (= (+ (* a a) (* b b)) (* c c)))

(display \"Sides: \")
(display sides)
(newline)
(display \"Is it a right triangle? \")
(display is-right?)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"Is it a right triangle? #t\"]

