### Example 73: Find the vertex of *y = x² - 4x + 7*

Complete the square: *y = (x - 2)² + 3*, so vertex is (2, 3).

<!-- BUILD: compute vertex by completing the square manually -->

```scheme
(define find-vertex-manual
  (let ((a 1)
        (b -4)
        (c 7))
    ;; vertex x-coordinate: h = -b / 2a
    (let* ((h (/ (- b) (* 2 a)))
           (k (+ (* a h h) (* b h) c)))
      (list h k))))

(display \"Vertex of y = x² - 4x + 7: \")
(display find-vertex-manual)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: text output showing \"(2, 3)\"]

